Package pl.polsl.model

Class MatrixCalculatorModel

java.lang.Object
pl.polsl.model.MatrixCalculatorModel
public class MatrixCalculatorModel extends Object
The MatrixCalculatorModel class provides functionalities for performing matrix operations such as addition, subtraction, and multiplication. It supports two matrices and uses Lombok to reduce boilerplate code.

    • addMatrices

      public List<List<Integer>> addMatrices() throws MatrixOperationException
      Adds two matrices (matrix1 and matrix2) element-wise.
      Returns:
      a new matrix representing the element-wise addition of matrix1 and matrix2.
      Throws:
      MatrixOperationException - if the matrices are not set or if their dimensions do not match.

    • subtractMatrices

      public List<List<Integer>> subtractMatrices() throws MatrixOperationException
      Subtracts matrix2 from matrix1 element-wise using a stream operation.
      Returns:
      a new matrix representing the element-wise subtraction of matrix2 from matrix1.
      Throws:
      MatrixOperationException - if the matrices do not have the same dimensions.

    • multiplyMatrices

      public MatrixRecord multiplyMatrices(MatrixRecord matrix1, MatrixRecord matrix2) throws MatrixOperationException
      Multiplies two matrices (matrix1 and matrix2) following matrix multiplication rules.
      Parameters:
      matrix1 - the first matrix record to multiply.
      matrix2 - the second matrix record to multiply.
      Returns:
      a MatrixRecord representing the result of the matrix multiplication.
      Throws:
      MatrixOperationException - if the number of columns in matrix1 does not match the number of rows in matrix2.
